From f475c95403be3943746e1e19e3ff7481c06c05ec Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: fi3 <email@email.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 08:17:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] FIX strip Cargo test binary paths so process checks run
 the apps

Cargo can execute integration-test binaries through hashed names under target/debug/deps, which made argv parsing and sibling orchestrator lookup treat executable paths as user input or resolve the wrong daemon path. Recognize those binary names, resolve the orchestrator from the target directory, keep the launch-error fixture on the in-process path, and make the localhost daemon test report startup stderr while skipping only the sandbox case where loopback bind is denied.
---
 src/cli.rs                 | 41 ++++++++++++++++++++++++--
 src/http_controller.rs     | 59 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 tests/cli.rs               | 23 +++++++++++++--
 tests/http_orchestrator.rs | 35 ++++++++++++++++------
 tests/start_script.rs      | 20 +++++++++----
 tests/terminal_pty.rs      |  1 +
 6 files changed, 153 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)

